8\/tommy-cornilleau-c-osAj9z0KQ-unsplash-1024x591.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/tommy-cornilleau-c-osAj9z0KQ-unsplash-300x173.jpg 300w, https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/tommy-cornilleau-c-osAj9z0KQ-unsplash-768x443.jpg 768w, https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/tommy-cornilleau-c-osAj9z0KQ-unsplash-1536x886.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/tommy-cornilleau-c-osAj9z0KQ-unsplash-2048x1182.jpg 2048w, https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/tommy-cornilleau-c-osAj9z0KQ-unsplash-780x450.jpg 780w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 980px) 100vw, 980px\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-3982a19 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"3982a19\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_has_onepagescroll_dot&quot;:&quot;yes&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-24cc437 e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"24cc437\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_has_onepagescroll_dot&quot;:&quot;yes&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-4704590 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"4704590\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h3>Itinerary<\/h3><p><b>Morning:<\/b><\/p><p>Bahia Palace: Start the day with a visit to the beautiful Bahia Palace, famous for its intricate Moroccan architecture and peaceful gardens.<\/p><p>Saadian Tombs: Explore the fascinating Saadian Tombs, a historical site dating back to the 16th century, home to the remains of the Saadian dynasty.<\/p><p>Koutoubia Mosque: Visit the majestic Koutoubia Mosque, the largest in Marrakech, known for its stunning minaret and beautiful gardens.<\/p><p><b>Afternoon:<\/b><\/p><p>Jemaa el-Fna Square: Discover the lively heart of the city with a walk through Jemaa el-Fna, where you&#8217;ll encounter street performers, food stalls, and vibrant market activity.<\/p><p>Souks of Marrakech: Wander through the colorful souks, where you can shop for unique Moroccan crafts, textiles, spices, jewelry, and more.<\/p><p>Majorelle Garden (Optional): For those interested in art and nature, visit the famous Majorelle Garden, once owned by Yves Saint Laurent, showcasing a blend of vibrant colors and exotic plants.<\/p><p><b style=\"color: var( --e-global-color-text );\">Additional Options for Half Day Tour<\/b><\/p><p>For those with less time, you can opt for a half-day tour, which will include either the morning or afternoon portion of the full-day tour.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>One-Day Private Guided Tour of Marrakech Experience the best of Marrakech in a private one-day tour, tailored to your preferences. Explore the city\u2019s vibrant culture, history, and stunning architecture with an expert guide who will help you discover Marrakech&#8217;s secrets and hidden gems. Itinerary Morning: Bahia Palace: Start the day with a visit to the [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":5,"featured_media":0,"parent":11313,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_active":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_note":"","_monsterinsights_sitenote_category":0,"footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-12595","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/12595","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/5"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=12595"}],"version-history":[{"count":7,"href":"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/12595\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":12800,"href":"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/12595\/revisions\/12800"}],"up":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/11313"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=12595"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}